revision.text:
A '''FON1 font''', or '''console font''', contains a set of 256 grayscaled, monospaced characters. It begins with a header of this form: {| !Offset !! Length !! Name !! Content |- |0x0000 || 4*1 || Identifier || The characters 'F', 'O', 'N', and '1'. |- |0x0004 || 2 || Width || Unsigned value for character width. |- |0x0006 || 2 || Height || Unsigned value for character height. |- |0x0008 || * || Data || RLE-compressed data for all characters in sequence. |}
The data create a ''Width'' &times; (''Height'' &times; 256) grayscale image in which the glyphs are in sequence from top to bottom. The darkest color, 0x00, is transparent.
[[ZDoom]] provides a FON1 font in a file named <tt>confont.lmp</tt> in zdoom.pk3. This is used for the console font. [[Category:Font formats]]
